Question:
This displacement-time graph shows the first 10 seconds of Mo's journey.

During that time he travelled at a speed of 6 \mathrm{~m} / \mathrm{s.}

What distance should replace the star?

Incorrect Answer:
\begin{array}{c@{}c@{}c@{}c}
    1.3 \\
  + 0.256 \\
  \hline
\end{array}

(This alignment incorrectly results in adding 3 and the 6 in the hundredth place, instead of aligning the decimal points)

